      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "APPEAL (1) continues to build a strong record and was impressive winner in quick time last start when scoring by 3.5 lengths (25.22) at Q Lakeside. Superior out of the boxes and will be in the firing line early. Winner at her latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Looks a key chance if runs up to latest figure. HARA'S FRANKIE (2) goes very well this course and distance starting 11 times for five wins and five minors. Recorded a 0.8 lengths win (20.19) in a Grade 5 last time at Capalaba. Can feature with the right run. ZIPPING MEHARY (3) had the drop on the lead and went on to be beaten 3.5 lengths into third (25.72) at Q Lakeside in a Grade 5 over 457m. Will give a great sight again. TAHITIAN GIRL (7) has ability and can feature with the right run after missing a cheque here most recently.",
